# CustomWaypoints architecture rules

- Carbonite is the map/rendering/low-level target backend.
- CustomWaypoints owns the queue, known locations, learned transports, route expansion, import/export, UI, and sync policy.
- `CustomWaypointsDB.destinations` is the active queue source of truth.
- Carbonite targets are a projection only and must not become source of truth.
- Do not reintroduce a separate transport-management UI. Known Locations manages routes, transports, and instances.
- Keep ordinary waypoint import as replace-queue. Keep known-location import as merge + dedupe.
- Preserve WotLK 3.3.5a compatibility. Avoid retail-only API assumptions.
- Prefer existing Carbonite map functions and CW helpers over new coordinate/math systems.
